properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 23 at 2:28AM CST until January 24 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...FREEZING DRIZZLE AND SNOW...

.Freezing drizzle will continue in the Twin Ports area this
morning but will change over to mainly light snow later this
morning. Then a prolonged period of light snow is expected today
into tonight, diminishing on Friday. Mostly snow is expected over
Ashland and Bayfield Counties and higher accumulation is looking
more likely across the higher terrain of the Bayfield Peninsula.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches,
except 5 to 8 inches for the higher terrain of northern Bayfield
county.

* WHERE...Bayfield and Ashland Counties. This includes the
Tribal Lands of the Red Cliff Band and the Bad River
Reservation.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM CST FRIDAY
